title: US interest rates increased despite worst banking turmoil since 2008
description: The Federal Reserve - the US central bank, known as the Fed - has increased interest rates for the ninth time in a row.

title: Gwyneth Paltrow's accuser 'deteriorated abruptly' after actress crashed into him, court told
description: Gwyneth Paltrow's accuser "deteriorated abruptly" after the US actress allegedly crashed into the back of him on the ski slopes, a court has been told.

title: K-pop star issues 'sincere apology' for wearing Nazi swastika on T-shirt
description: Chaeyoung, a member of Twice - one of the most globally successful K-pop groups - has "sincerely apologised" after wearing a T-shirt featuring a Nazi swastika.

title: Taliban can give evidence to inquiry into 'unlawful killings' by British soldiers, says judge
description: A senior judge has called for evidence relating to allegations of unlawful activity by British armed forces in Afghanistan from anyone - including the Taliban.

title: Prince William makes secret visit to Polish and British troops near Ukraine border
description: Prince William has made a secret trip to Poland to "personally thank" Polish and British troops supporting Ukraine.

title: 'So many are already dead': France ordered to ban fishing to protect dolphins amid 'serious danger of extinction'
description: The French government has been ordered to ban fishing off parts of its western coastline amid fears the common dolphin is in "serious danger" of becoming extinct.

title: What killed Beethoven? Genome sequencing of composer's hair finds likely cause
description: Scientists have analysed locks of what is believed to be Ludwig van Beethoven’s hair to sequence the genome of the prodigious composer - finding the likely combination behind his death at 56-years-old, as well as a potential affair in his paternal line.

title: The risks of depleted uranium after Putin's nuclear warning to UK
description: Russia has accused the UK of increasing the chances of a "nuclear collision" by supplying Ukraine with armour-piercing depleted uranium tank shells.

title: Uganda passes bill making it a crime to identify as LGBT - with death penalty for 'aggravated homosexuality'
description: Uganda has passed a bill to make it a crime to identify as LGBT - with the death penalty for "aggravated homosexuality".

title: Joe Biden hints at re-election bid while honouring Bruce Springsteen
description: US President Joe Biden quipped that he is seeking a "back-to-back" term in the White House while honouring famous figures including Bruce Springsteen and Vera Wang.

title: New CCTV footage released of man 'smothered to death' by US police
description: The final minutes of a man who was "smothered to death" after as many as ten police officers and medical staff appeared to sit on him for 12 minutes were captured in newly-released CCTV footage.
